  "response_text": "An animated scene opens inside a dim wooden barn arranged like a meeting hall. A small stage made of planks sits under a bright hanging bulb, with ropes, hay, a wagon wheel, and farm tools around the walls. A crowd of turkeys fills the lower area, all facing the stage. Onstage, a tall, cartoonish turkey with a green head, orange beak, red wattle, brown body, and fanned tail stands like a presenter. Beside him is an easel holding a large flip chart with a picture of a Kraft Miracle Whip jar on it. Other turkeys stand nearby like assistants or concerned onlookers.\n\nThe lead turkey gestures broadly with his wings and a pointer, addressing the crowd. He leans over a small stand or lectern, then steps forward, his tail spread behind him. His face is expressive, with wide eyes, heavy brows, and a long red wattle swinging over his beak as he talks. The Miracle Whip chart remains clearly visible at his side, showing a white jar with a blue lid and the red “Miracle Whip” logo. As he continues, he moves close to the chart and points toward it, while turkeys in the audience stare up at him with anxious, open-mouthed expressions.\n\nThe speaker struts along the front of the stage, passing in front of the crowd. Seen from the audience level, his legs and body move across the foreground while rows of turkeys watch from below. Several turkeys have pale green or bluish heads, orange beaks, dangling red wattles, and rounded feathered bodies. Some look alarmed, some confused, and several have their beaks hanging open. The barn lights glow warmly overhead, contrasting with darker blue shadows in the background.\n\nThe lead turkey returns to the easel. He flips the chart page, replacing the jar-only image with a poster that reads, in large black letters, “MIRACLE WHIP MAKES A BETTER TURKEY SANDWICH!” Beneath the words is a picture of a young girl eating a sandwich, with a Miracle Whip jar shown beside her. The poster fills much of the right side as the turkey stands beside it with his pointer raised. His eyes widen and his mouth opens dramatically, as if emphasizing the bad news for turkeys. He leans in close to the poster, his beak and face looming large, while the printed child and product remain in the background.\n\nThe audience reacts with shock. Three turkeys are shown close together, their long necks stretched upward, eyes wide, and beaks open. One bluish-headed turkey in the middle appears especially startled, while another pale green turkey beside him turns with a worried look. The crowd then erupts into motion. Turkeys scramble and flap around in the dim barn, and one brown turkey tumbles onto its back with its feet and wings up, surrounded by others milling about in panic.\n\nBack onstage, the lead turkey stands between two lighter-colored turkeys, still in front of the Miracle Whip sandwich poster. He raises both wings and gestures as though presenting a new plan. The turkeys beside him watch with uncertain expressions. Then another bird brings in costume-like pieces: a large yellow duck bill and oversized yellow webbed feet. Close-up, feathered hands push and adjust a bright yellow rubbery duck foot, fitting it onto a turkey’s foot. Large pale tail feathers briefly fill the view like fans as the disguise is assembled.\n\nThe lead turkey emerges in a duck disguise. He now wears enormous yellow webbed feet and a duck-like bill or beak extension strapped over his face, while his turkey tail still fans behind him. He poses upright on the wooden stage with his wings lifted, trying to look like a duck, though his turkey body remains obvious. He waddles and flaps, shifting his weight awkwardly from one big yellow foot to the other. The Miracle Whip poster with the girl and sandwich still stands on the easel to his right, making the contrast comic: he is trying to escape being recognized as a turkey while the poster warns about turkey sandwiches.\n\nHe continues the duck act, bobbing and turning, then stumbles and twists as the oversized feet make him clumsy. In the crowd, two pale turkeys in the foreground look on from above or from a raised area, their faces partly in shadow. One turns toward the other with a skeptical, unimpressed expression while the disguised turkey blurs in the background on the stage, still performing his awkward duck routine.\n\nThe animated barn scene gives way to a bright, real kitchen and dining area. A school-age girl with dark hair in pigtails sits at a table beside an adult man. Both hold sandwiches in their hands and take bites. The girl wears a pink-and-white top, and the man wears a dark green open shirt over a light undershirt. A woman in a green top is visible in the background at the kitchen counter. The room is softly lit with pendant lamps, pale cabinetry, and a relaxed home atmosphere. On the table at the left is a jar of Kraft Miracle Whip with its blue lid and red logo, along with plates and glasses of water.\n\nThe girl chews happily while holding her sandwich with both hands. The man pauses and glances toward her while holding his own sandwich over a plate. The Miracle Whip jar remains visible on the table, tying the family meal to the product shown earlier in the animated barn.\n\nA close view shows Miracle Whip being spread onto a slice of white bread with a knife. The creamy white sauce covers the bread in a smooth layer. Next to it sits the Miracle Whip jar, label facing forward, and nearby are sandwich ingredients including sliced tomatoes, lettuce, and stacks of turkey slices or deli meat. The final image presents the product neatly: a Kraft Miracle Whip jar stands on a countertop beside a finished turkey sandwich layered with bread, meat, tomato, and greens, with a pickle wedge nearby. The jar’s blue lid and red “Miracle Whip” logo are centered clearly for recognition.",
